| Notes                   = * Filming for this film started in late July, 2019,{{cite|ref=true|url= https://ew.com/comic-con/2019/07/21/angelina-jolie-the-eternals-exclusive-cast-portrait/|title= See the exclusive first portrait of Angelina Jolie and the cast of The Eternals|work= EW|last= Bucksbaum|first= Sydney|date= July 21, 2019|accessdate= July 24, 2019}} and wrapped on February 4, 2020.{{cite|ref=true|url= https://www.digitalspy.com/movies/a30768076/marvel-phase-four-the-eternals-filming-wrapped-gemma-chan/|title= Marvel's The Eternals star Gemma Chan confirms Phase 4 movie has wrapped filming|work= Digital Spy|last= Chase|first= Stephanie|date= February 4, 2020|accessdate= February 14, 2020}}
* The film was originally scheduled to release on November 6, 2020.<ref name="D23 2019"/> However, on April 3, 2020, Marvel announced its Phase Four film line-up had been pushed back due to the {{WP|COVID-19 pandemic|COVID-19 pandemic}}, with ''Eternals'' taking the new release date of February 12, 2021.{{cite|ref=true|url= https://variety.com/2020/film/box-office/disney-mulan-black-widow-release-dates-coronavirus-1203550173/|title= ‘Black Widow,’ ‘Eternals,’ ‘Indiana Jones 5’ and More Disney Films Get New Release Dates|work= Variety|last= Rubin|first= Rebecca|date= April 3, 2020|accessdate= April 3, 2020}} In September 2020, the film was pushed back again to November 5, 2021.{{cite|ref=true|url=https://variety.com/2020/film/news/black-widow-west-side-story-eternals-release-date-delay-1234773491/|title=‘Black Widow,’ ‘West Side Story,’ ‘Eternals’ Postpone Release Dates|accessdate=24 September 2020|last=Lang|first=Brent|coauthors=Rubin, Rebecca|date=23 September 2020|work=Variety}}
| Trivia                  = * Gemma Chan had previously portrayed the [[Earth-199999|Marvel Cinematic Universe]]-character [[Minn-Erva (Earth-199999)|Minn-Erva]] in the film {{sl|Captain Marvel (film)}}.
** On being recast from her role in ''Captain Marvel'', Chan stated that Marvel Studios head Kevin Feige told her that they'd love to work with her again and that they "wanted to make better use" of her acting talents.{{cite|ref=true|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/gemma-chan-on-let-them-all-talk-and-how-she-wound-up-in-eternals-after-captain-marvel|title=Gemma Chan on 'Let Them All Talk' and How She Wound Up in 'Eternals' After 'Captain Marvel'|last=Davis|first=Brian|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=11 December 2020|accessdate=13 December 2020|}}
